description: One out of every twelve men and one out of every two hundred women are born color challenged.  "Color blindness" is a common eye condition that makes it difficult to distinguish between certain colors. A person that is "colorblind" does not have any form of blindness but simply experiences problems determining colors like yellow, red, blue or green.  Take this simple test or have a loved one take this test to determine if you may be Color Challenged.  Am I Color Challenged randomly generates tests that require only a few screen taps to complete. This application includes the tests and suggestions and links to help.
